   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Ultrasonic vocalizations from mice\n",
    "Mouse USVs do not cluster into discrete types but lie on a continuous, low-dimensional manifold.\n",
    "\n",
    "We here closely follow the procedure described in Sainburg et al. (2020): Finding, visualizing, and quantifying latent structure across (see code on [github](https://github.com/timsainb/avgn_paper))."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2020-08-27T09:07:52.082Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2020-08-27T09:07:52.075Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2020-08-27T09:07:55.043Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2020-08-27T09:07:55.069Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import librosa.feature\n",
    "import colorcet as cc\n",
    "import umap\n",
    "import scipy.cluster.vq\n",
    "import das_unsupervised.spec_utils\n",
    "from io import BytesIO\n",
    "import urllib.request\n",
    "\n",
    "%config InlineBackend.figure_format = 'jpg'  # smaller mem footprint for page\n",
    "plt.style.use('ncb.mplstyle')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Download audio data\n",
    "Data kindly provided by Kurt Hammerschmidt and published in A Ivanenko, P Watkins, MAJ van Gerven, K Hammerschmidt, B Englitz (2020) Classifying sex and strain from mouse ultrasonic vocalizations using deep learning. PLoS Comput Biol 16(6): e1007918.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "url = 'https://github.com/janclemenslab/das_unsupervised/releases/download/v0.4/mice.npz'\n",
    "with urllib.request.urlopen(url) as f:\n",
    "    ff = BytesIO(f.read())\n",
    "\n",
    "d = np.load(ff)\n",
    "samplerate = d['samplerate']\n",
    "recording = d['recording']\n",
    "syllable_onsets = d['syllable_onsets']\n",
    "syllable_offsets = d['syllable_offsets']"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Pre-processing\n",
    "Compute the spectrogram"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2020-08-27T09:07:57.144Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2020-08-27T09:07:57.138Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2020-08-27T09:08:06.680Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2020-08-27T09:08:06.708Z"
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "(128,)\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/jpeg": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1440x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "n_fft = 2048\n",
    "hop_length = int(samplerate / 1000)\n",
    "\n",
    "specgram = librosa.feature.melspectrogram(recording, sr=samplerate, n_fft=n_fft, hop_length=hop_length, power=1, fmin=40_000)\n",
    "freqs = librosa.core.mel_frequencies(n_mels=specgram.shape[0], fmin=40_000, fmax=int(samplerate/2), htk=False)\n",
    "sm = np.median(specgram, axis=1)\n",
    "print(sm.shape)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(20, 4))\n",
    "plt.imshow(np.log2(specgram[:, int(syllable_onsets[1]/hop_length)-10:int(syllable_offsets[4]/hop_length)+10]), cmap='cet_CET_L17')\n",
    "for onset, offset in zip(syllable_onsets[1:5], syllable_offsets[1:5]):\n",
    "    plt.axvline((onset-syllable_onsets[1])/hop_length + 10, c='k')\n",
    "    plt.axvline((offset-syllable_onsets[1])/hop_length + 10, c='k')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Extract and threshold syllables from spectrogram"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2020-08-27T09:08:06.691Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2020-08-27T09:08:06.687Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2020-08-27T09:08:09.469Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2020-08-27T09:08:09.510Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/jpeg": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 720x720 with 32 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "specs = [] \n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 10))\n",
    "for cnt, (onset, offset) in enumerate(zip(syllable_onsets, syllable_offsets)):\n",
    "    spec = np.log2(specgram[:, int(onset/hop_length):int(offset/hop_length)]/ sm[:,np.newaxis])\n",
    "    spec = spec[15:-10, :]\n",
    "    spec[spec<0] = 0\n",
    "    specs.append(spec)\n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        plt.subplot(4,4,cnt+1)\n",
    "        plt.imshow(spec, cmap='jet')\n",
    "        plt.xlim(0, 50)\n",
    "        plt.colorbar()\n",
    "    except:\n",
    "        pass"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Log-scale the time axis to reduce differences in syllable duration and zero-pad all syllables to the same duration"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2020-08-27T09:08:09.504Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2020-08-27T09:08:09.498Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2020-08-27T09:08:10.511Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2020-08-27T09:08:10.545Z"
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "46\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/jpeg": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 720x720 with 16 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "spec_rs = [das_unsupervised.spec_utils.log_resize_spec(spec, scaling_factor=8) for spec in specs]\n",
    "\n",
    "max_len = np.max([spec.shape[1] for spec in spec_rs])\n",
    "print(max_len)\n",
    "spec_rs = [das_unsupervised.spec_utils.pad_spec(spec, pad_length=max_len) for spec in spec_rs]\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 10))\n",
    "for cnt, spc in enumerate(spec_rs[:16]):\n",
    "    plt.subplot(4,4,cnt+1)\n",
    "    plt.imshow(spc, cmap='turbo')\n",
    "    plt.xlim(0, 50)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Center spectra around their peak frequencies"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2020-08-27T09:08:10.523Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2020-08-27T09:08:10.519Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2020-08-27T09:08:10.559Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2020-08-27T09:08:10.614Z"
    },
    "jupyter": {
     "outputs_hidden": false,
     "source_hidden": false
    },
    "nteract": {
     "transient": {
      "deleting": false
     }
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "offset = 20\n",
    "spec_rs_c = [das_unsupervised.spec_utils.center_spec(spec, halfwidth=offset) for spec in spec_rs]\n",
    "spec_rs_c = np.array(spec_rs_c)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Flatten 2D [time x freq] spectrograms to 1D feature vectors"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2020-08-27T09:08:10.575Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2020-08-27T09:08:10.569Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2020-08-27T09:08:10.584Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2020-08-27T09:08:10.618Z"
    },
    "jupyter": {
     "outputs_hidden": false,
     "source_hidden": false
    },
    "nteract": {
     "transient": {
      "deleting": false
     }
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "spec_flat = [spec.ravel() for spec in spec_rs_c]\n",
    "spec_flat = np.array(spec_flat)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Dimensionality reduction and clustering\n",
    "Embed the feature vectors into a 2D space using [UMAP](https://umap-learn.readthedocs.io/) and group similar syllables usign [kmeans](https://docs.scipy.org/doc/scipy/reference/generated/scipy.cluster.vq.kmeans2.html)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2020-08-27T09:08:10.597Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2020-08-27T09:08:10.592Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2020-08-27T09:08:19.017Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2020-08-27T09:08:19.049Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "/Users/clemens10/miniconda3/lib/python3.7/site-packages/scipy/cluster/vq.py:607: UserWarning: One of the clusters is empty. Re-run kmeans with a different initialization.\n",
      "  warnings.warn(\"One of the clusters is empty. \"\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "out = umap.UMAP(min_dist=0.5, random_state=2).fit_transform(spec_flat)\n",
    "k_centroid, k_labels = scipy.cluster.vq.kmeans2(out, k=40, seed=2)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Plot results\n",
    "Syllable spectrograms embedded into a 2D space  (left) and colored by the unsupervised cluster labels (right). Syllables do not fall into separate groups, but can be grouped by similarity using clustering."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2020-08-27T09:08:19.031Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2020-08-27T09:08:19.025Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2020-08-27T09:08:19.139Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2020-08-27T09:08:19.168Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/jpeg": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 720x360 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.subplot(121)\n",
    "plt.scatter(out[:,0], out[:,1], c='k', alpha=0.25, s=8)\n",
    "plt.axis('tight')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('UMAP 1')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('UMAP 2')\n",
    "plt.title('embedded syllables')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.subplot(122)\n",
    "plt.scatter(out[:,0], out[:,1], c=k_labels, cmap='cet_glasbey_dark', alpha=0.5, s=8, edgecolor='none')\n",
    "plt.axis('tight')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('UMAP 1')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('UMAP 2')\n",
    "plt.title('embedded syllables labelled by kmeans')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Average spectrograms of the syllables in each cluster, plotted at the position of the respective cluster centroid in UMAP space. Spectrotemporal features vary smoothly within this space, suggesting that mouse USVs lie on a low-dimensional manifold."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2020-08-27T09:08:19.900Z",

   "outputs": [

     "output_type": "display_data"

   ],
   "source": [
    "fig = plt.figure(figsize=(12, 12))\n",
    "ax = plt.axes()\n",
    "for cnt, (centroid, label) in enumerate(zip(k_centroid, np.unique(k_labels))):\n",
    "    idx = np.where(k_labels==label)[0]\n",
    "    X = np.mean(spec_rs_c[idx], axis=0)\n",
    "    fig.figimage(X=X, xo=centroid[0]*40, yo=centroid[1]*40, cmap='cet_CET_L17')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('UMAP 1')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('UMAP 2')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  }
 ],
